<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Using logarithms to compute a product</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
Given that:
\[
\log A = {@L_a@}, \quad \log B = {@L_b@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Use logarithms to find the value of:
</p>

<p>
\[
A \times B
\]
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to 3 decimal places.
</p>

<p>
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Step 1: Use the product rule:
</p>

<p>
\[
\text{log} (AB) = \text{log} A + \text{log} B
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
= {@L_a@} + {@L_b@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
= {@L_sum@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Take the antilogarithm:
</p>

<p>
\[
AB = 10^{@L_sum@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
= {@ans_round@}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
